    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-14T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="693"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/112: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-15T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >December 15, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 15—5:25
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. The Netherlands Minister on December 13 made formal representations to the
                    Japanese Government on the subject of the oil monopoly in Manchuria, leaving
                    with the Foreign Office an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> along
                    substantially the same lines as the British <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    of November 24. Full text by mail.<note n="83" xml:id="d693fn83">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated by mail to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
